ass=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 46<br> <font color=#333333>(4/11/01 8:24:02 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Dyeing of Armor</span><hr size=1> This is just me complaining about this topic. Why in the Nine Hells can we dye Fine Plate, but not robes? This makes no sense to me. I have posted this topic elsewhere before, I want to know what you all think. It bothers me sometimes when everywhere I go, I see my twin or someone with almost the exact same stuff as me. I know the items part can't be avoided, but I feel that if you could dye your robe/armor, no matter what type it was, that would rock. To be even more personalized, I don't think it would be that hard for them to make it so you could put symbols on your armor either. Even your shield. You would have to get a tailor to do it, or a blacksmith for the metal armor. Granted, I don't mean free reign on the symbols, otherwise you would see every druid with a symbol on his tunic with either &quot;SoW - DONT ASK.&quot; or &quot;TP - 50pp EACH!&quot;. hehe You get my idea, but maybe something along the lines of being able to get your character's deity symbol on the armor?<br>
<br>
I don't know, I think there needs to be a lot more personalization of the characters in EQ. So far, they have made 2 expansions with 2 new continents and one whole new race. They should take a couple days and offer some more faces and bodies for the races. It would be cool if the warrior didn't have the same build as the wizard. And my final and always pending question...&quot;Where the hell is my long white beard?&quot; <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
&quot;That's just my opinion. I could be wrong.&quot; =) <p><b><i>Xiltin Magisoul</i></b><br>
Gnomish Magician<br>
29th level - 8th Circle of Elemental Mastery<br>
Proud member of <i>The Sentinent</i><br>
<i>Lanys T'Vyl</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub30.ezboard.com/bthesentinent.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=gajiin>Gajiin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sentinent Officer and GI</span><br>  Posts: 186<br> <font color=#333333>(4/11/01 8:33:53 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Dyeing of Armor</span><hr size=1> You used to play UO, didnt you /grin...come on, you can tell us, we'll understand hehe. So did I. That was probably the most appealing part of that game : the ability to personalize your character to the point of being different from everyone else. Id even settle for the ability to chose the shade of dye for FS, that would be golden within itself. Funny thou, if this change did occur, all those hard to get crappy stat robes wouldnt sell anymore thou, cause some peeps just jack up the price cause they are new lookin. It would probably help the economy <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Good point bro. Now if they'd only give us straw hats to go with the fishing poles... <p>Xaijin, Shaddahkniggit <BR>
Keeper of the Screaming Spiroc</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub30.ezboard.com/ugermish.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Germish</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 57<br> <font color=#333333>(4/12/01 11:19:31 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Dyeing of Armor</span><hr size=1> *rises hand*  I played UO too.  That was one thing UO will always have over EQ, the trade skills.<br>
<br>
Anyway I think if would be a good idea if tailors could dye there goods, in the same way blacksmiths can. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub30.ezboard.com/uxiltinmagisoul.showPublicProfile?language=EN>XiltinMagisoul</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 47<br> <font color=#333333>(4/12/01 11:57:40 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Dyeing of Armor</span><hr size=1> Aye, guilty of UO here too. =) I didn't play it very long though because that game in itself redefined the meaning of LAG. Especially for me on a modem connection, which at that point in technology, was good enough. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Basically, me and some friends sat around and dyed our clothes and hats and then conned people out of their horses.. LOL I got so frustrated with trying to level that I gave up. Finding reagents for being a caster in that game was ridiculous and I got tired of the rabbits kicking my ass.  hehe <p><b><i>Xiltin Magisoul</i></b><br>
